This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and the comparison of contextualized word representations produced by different models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning models such as ELMo, BERT, and GPT-2, which are commonly used in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also briefly mentions the use of embeddings in computer vision tasks, which could potentially place it in the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV).
